Model Year Start: 2016 Model: Prius Prod Date Range: [11/2015 -           ]
Title: SEAT: REAR SEAT ASSEMBLY: REASSEMBLY; 2016 - 2022 MY Prius [11/2015 -        ]

REASSEMBLY

CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT

CAUTION:

Wear protective gloves. Sharp areas on the parts may injure your hands.

PROCEDURE

1. INSTALL BENCH TYPE REAR SEAT CUSHION COVER

HINT:

When installing a bench type rear seat cushion cover, refer to Precaution in order to prevent wrinkles from forming.

Click here

(a) Engage the 18 claws.

NOTICE:

Be careful not to damage the bench type rear seat cushion cover.

(b) Engage the 19 hooks.

NOTICE:

Be careful not to damage the bench type rear seat cushion cover.

(c) Engage the 2 fasteners and hook to install the bench type rear seat cushion cover to the rear seat cushion pad.

NOTICE:

Be careful not to damage the bench type rear seat cushion cover.

*a

Fastener

2. INSTALL REAR SEATBACK LOCK ASSEMBLY LH (for LH Side)

(a) Install the rear seatback lock assembly LH to the rear seatback frame sub-assembly LH with the 2 bolts.

Torque:

30 N·m {306 kgf·cm, 22 ft·lbf}

3. INSTALL SEPARATE TYPE REAR SEATBACK COVER (for LH Side)

HINT:

When installing a separate type rear seatback cover, refer to Precaution in order to prevent wrinkles from forming.

Click here

(a) Engage the 8 claws to install the separate type rear seatback cover to the separate type rear seatback pad LH.

NOTICE:

Be careful not to damage the separate type rear seatback cover.

4. INSTALL SEPARATE TYPE REAR SEATBACK COVER WITH PAD (for LH Side)

(a) Install the separate type rear seatback cover with pad to the rear seatback frame sub-assembly LH as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

(b) Engage the 4 claws to install the 2 rear seat headrest supports as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

5. INSTALL REAR SEATBACK BOARD SUB-ASSEMBLY LH (for LH Side)

(a) Engage the 2 guides.

(b) Engage the 5 claws to install the rear seatback board sub-assembly LH.

(c) Close the 2 fasteners as shown in the illustration.

*a

Fastener

(d) Engage the hook.

6. INSTALL REAR SEATBACK LOCK CONTROL BEZEL (for LH Side)

(a) Engage the 4 claws to install a new rear seatback lock control bezel.

7. INSTALL REAR SEATBACK LOCK ASSEMBLY RH (for RH Side)

(a) Install the rear seatback lock assembly RH to the rear seatback frame sub-assembly RH with the 2 bolts.

Torque:

30 N·m {306 kgf·cm, 22 ft·lbf}

8. INSTALL REAR CENTER SEAT OUTER BELT ASSEMBLY (for RH Side)

Click here

9. INSTALL SEPARATE TYPE REAR SEATBACK COVER (for RH Side)

HINT:

When installing a separate type rear seatback cover, refer to Precaution in order to prevent wrinkles from forming.

Click here

(a) Engage the 8 claws to install the separate type rear seatback cover to the separate type rear seatback pad RH.

NOTICE:

Be careful not to damage the separate type rear seatback cover.

10. INSTALL SEPARATE TYPE REAR SEATBACK COVER WITH PAD (for RH Side)

(a) Pass the rear center seat outer belt assembly through the separate type rear seatback cover with pad and temporarily install the separate type rear seatback cover with pad to the rear seatback frame sub-assembly RH as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

(b) for RH Side:

Install in this Direction

(1) Engage the 4 claws to install the 2 rear seat headrest supports as shown in the illustration.

(c) for Center:

Install in this Direction

(1) Engage the 4 claws to install the 2 rear seat headrest supports as shown in the illustration.

(d) Engage the hook to install the separate type rear seatback cover with pad to the rear seatback frame sub-assembly RH.

11. INSTALL REAR SEATBACK BOARD SUB-ASSEMBLY RH (for RH Side)

(a) Engage the 2 guides.

(b) Engage the 9 claws to install the rear seatback board sub-assembly RH.

(c) Close the 2 fasteners as shown in the illustration.

*a

Fastener

(d) Engage the hook.

12. INSTALL REAR SEATBACK LOCK CONTROL BEZEL (for RH Side)

(a) Engage the 4 claws to install a new rear seatback lock control bezel.

13. INSTALL REAR SEAT SHOULDER BELT COVER (for RH Side)

(a) Install the rear seat shoulder belt cover.

14. INSTALL SEAT BELT ANCHOR COVER CAP (for RH Side)

(a) Engage the 2 guides to install the seat belt anchor cover cap as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

(b) Engage the 2 guides and 2 claws to connect the rear seat shoulder belt cover with seat belt anchor cover cap.

15. INSTALL REAR SEAT CENTER ARMREST ASSEMBLY (for RH Side)

(a) Install the bush as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

(b) Engage the pin as shown in the illustration.

(c) Engage the guide as shown in the illustration.

(d) Install the rear seat center armrest assembly with the bolt and washer.

Torque:

21 N·m {214 kgf·cm, 15 ft·lbf}

16. INSTALL CENTER ARMREST HINGE COVER (for RH Side)

(a) Engage the claw to install the center armrest hinge cover as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction
